%N A331352 Number of chiral pairs of colorings of the edges (or triangular faces) of a regular 4-dimensional simplex with n available colors.
%C A331352 A 4-dimensional simplex has 5 vertices and 10 edges. Its Schläfli symbol is {3,3,3}. The chiral colorings of its edges come in pairs, each the reflection of the other.
%H A331352 <a href="/index/Rec#order_11">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (11,-55,165,-330,462,-462,330,-165,55,-11,1).
%F A331352 a(n) = (24*n^2 - 50*n^3 + 20*n^4 + 15*n^6 - 10*n^7 + n^10) / 120.
%F A331352 a(n) = 6*C(n,2) + 387*C(n,3) + 6320*C(n,4) + 41350*C(n,5) + 135792*C(n,6) + 246540*C(n,7) + 252000*C(n,8) + 136080*C(n,9) + 30240*C(n,10), where the coefficient of C(n,k) is the number of colorings using exactly k colors.
%F A331352 a(n) = A331350(n) - A063843(n) = (A331350(n) - A331353(n)) / 2 = A063843(n) - A331353(n).
%F A331352 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Jun 02 2026: (Start)
%F A331352 G.f.: x^2*(6 + 339*x + 3779*x^2 + 11221*x^3 + 10717*x^4 + 3681*x^5 + 473*x^6 + 23*x^7 + x^8) / (1 - x)^11.
%F A331352 E.g.f.: exp(x)*x^2*(360 + 7740*x + 31600*x^2 + 41350*x^3 + 22632*x^4 + 5870*x^5 + 750*x^6 + 45*x^7 + x^8) / 120.
%F A331352 a(n) = 11*a(n-1) - 55*a(n-2) + 165*a(n-3) - 330*a(n-4) + 462*a(n-5) - 462*a(n-6) + 330*a(n-7) - 165*a(n-8) + 55*a(n-9) - 11*a(n-10) + a(n-11). (End)
%t A331352 Table[(24n^2 - 50n^3 + 20n^4 + 15n^6 - 10n^7 + n^10)/120, {n, 1, 25}]
%Y A331352 Cf. A331350 (oriented), A063843 (unoriented), A331353 (achiral).
